nmapeople.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Anarchy Online?</span><hr size=1> Whats everyone's opinion of the game so far? I hear some good things as well as bad things..... hopefully as soon as I get a new 'puter I'll be able to come on and play with everyone  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/faleaus/bwgenma.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/usetis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Setis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#778899>(7/31/01 2:42:13 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anarchy Online?</span><hr size=1> Game = good<br>
Infrastructure = bad<br>
<br>
'nuff said. <p><B>Setis Dagre</B><BR>
<B>Ice Clan</B><BR>
<I>"Some people like to stand out in the rain without an umbrella.  That's what it means to live free."<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ugrottnikk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grottnikk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#778899>(8/1/01 9:50:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> to elaborate</span><hr size=1> The concepts are great - you can group or go solo and still get xp, you dont have to worry about over-camping, the difference between classes is cool, and the veritable shit-load of items, armour, implants and nanos (spells) is really cool.  Hell, you can even construct your own items if you wanna.<br>
<br>
On the downside, though, there are constant crashes, bad framerates due to memory leaks in the game, servers are down lots for patches/maintenance, and there are still some other bugs.<br>
<br>
I can play the game now without too much worry.  Occasionally i'll crash and lose some progress, and that's a piss-off, but the game is good enough to keep me coming back for more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uwarangel1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarAngel1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#778899>(8/3/01 6:18:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: to elaborate</span><hr size=1> <br>
  I think the game rocks.  System requirements from funcom are bull though, I would suggest minimum setup something like this :<br>
<br>
P3-700+<br>
256 Meg RAM<br>
Fast 3d card (ie Radeon, Geforce Ultra Pro etc or faster)<br>
<br>
I was using a P3-800 OC'd to 880 w/256 meg of ram, and the game ran good in outdoors zones but really choppy in crowded city areas.  Upgrading from that to an Athalon 1.2Ghz with 512 meg RAM made the game *much* better.  RAM is the major factor, 256 is *barely* enough for this game, with 512meg youll zone almost instantly and in crowded city areas lag is not too bad.  Im going to guess that 128meg would make it pretty close to unplayable in any crowded area, although the last couple of patches seem to have reduced lag considerably.<br>
<br>
The graphics, well, played EQ a few times after playing AO and suffice it to say I never realized how dated EQ looks now.  The game is much more fun than eq - there is always something to do.  No more sitting around lfg for hours or long boring corpse retrievals for me.  Groups are easy to find, and the world in AO is massive compared to EQ.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
Teer 59 Templar &lt;Institute&gt;<br>
Dakinis 30 Adventurer (AO)<br>
